[{"id":"VR797901","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a sphere suspended by a string that hangs at an angle of theta from the vertical.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR797901.g01.svg\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A small insulating sphere of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"m\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> and charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive q\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"positive q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi></mpadded></math></span></span> hangs from a string with negligible mass near the surface of Earth, as shown in the figure. A uniform electric field is directed horizontally, causing the sphere to hang with the string at an angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"theta\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>Î¸</mi></math></span></span> from the vertical. Suppose that a different sphere hangs from a string on the surface of the Moon, where the acceleration due to gravity is approximately <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one sixth\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"one sixth\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math></span></span> times that of Earth. Which of the following modifications could be made so that the sphere and string hang at the same angle on the Moon as on Earth?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR797901_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Increase the mass by a factor of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> and decrease the charge by a factor of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Decrease the mass by a factor of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> and increase the charge by a factor of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Increase the charge by a factor of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> and decrease the electric field by a factor of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Decrease the charge by a factor of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> and increase the electric field by a factor of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>.</p>"],"answer":0}]